Description: Drop the hf-xet platform-guarded install requirement
 Upstream's setup.py lists `hf-xet >= 1.1.3` as an install requirement
 on x86_64/amd64/arm64/aarch64. hf-xet is a Rust-based accelerator
 for the Hugging Face Xet object-store protocol; it is not packaged
 anywhere in Noble. Every reference to it inside the huggingface_hub
 source is wrapped in `try: import hf_xet ... except ImportError:`,
 so the HTTP-only paths Avalan exercises (model.from_pretrained,
 plain file downloads) work without it. Drop the line so dh_python3
 does not turn an absent Noble package into an unresolvable
 Depends, and so apt-get install does not refuse the binary build.
Author: Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-18

--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -14,7 +14,6 @@
 install_requires = [
     "filelock",
     "fsspec>=2023.5.0",
-    "hf-xet>=1.1.3,<2.0.0; platform_machine=='x86_64' or platform_machine=='amd64' or platform_machine=='arm64' or platform_machine=='aarch64'",
     "packaging>=20.9",
     "pyyaml>=5.1",
     "requests",
